 Nationalty both in home affairs and in foreign policy. In this manner this title is able to bring the state doctrine and its role in Russian history into proper focus.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union. 0aNationalismzSoviet Union. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520341449?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520341449423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520341449/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles